<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911007-0160</DOCNO><DOCID>911007-0160.</DOCID><HL>   BI to Post Fiscal 1st-Period Loss</HL><DATE>10/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BIAC</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)</NS><RE>COLORADO (CO)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   BOULDER, Colo. -- BI Inc., blaming the recession, said itwill report a loss and a decline in revenue for its firstquarter, which ended last Monday.   In the first quarter last year, BI had net income of$497,000, or 10 cents a share, on revenue of $3.7 million.</LP><TEXT>   The manufacturer of electronic identification andmonitoring systems said that state and local governments,which buy its monitoring equipment for correctionsdepartments, have held back purchases because of tightbudgets.</TEXT></DOC>